release checklist:
1. Check the output of the test suite
2. Check the output of the example programs
3. Check the output of 'git status' - is everything in the repository?
4. Version numbers
4a. Have you set the VERSION string in the Makefile to the new version?
4b. Check above if the version number and date are set correctly in the Changes file
5. Run 'make release'
6. Check the contents of the source code package
7. Check the contents of the binary package
8. Create the release announcement
9. Add the new version to the website
10. Commit the website changes
11. Create a git tag
12. Copy announcement and the packages to the website: 'make copy-website copy-packages-website'
